The '''''Camion Équipé d'un Système d'Artillerie''''' (English: "Truck equipped with an artillery system") or '''CAESAR'''<ref name="DF">{{cite web
| url= http://www.defense-update.com/products/c/caesar.htm| title= Caesar self propelled cannon| date= 26 July 2006| website= Defense Update| url-status   = dead | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20071021193521/http://defense-update.com/products/c/caesar.htm| archive-date = 21 October 2007| access-date= 21 June 2024}}</ref> is a French [[155 mm]], 52-caliber [[self-propelled gun]] that can fire 39/52 caliber NATO-standard shells. It is installed on a [[Six-wheel drive|6×6]] or [[Eight-wheel drive|8×8]] truck chassis. Equipped with an autonomous weapon network incorporating an inertial navigation system and ballistic computer, the CAESAR can accurately strike targets more than {{convert|40|km|mi}} away using "Extended Range, Full Bore" (ERFB) ammunition with [[base bleed]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=155 mm HE ER FB-BB (OFd M3-DV) |author= |website= msm.sk| publisher= MSM Group |date= |access-date=29 July 2022 |url= https://www.msm.sk/en/what-we-do/defence/ammunition/artillery-ammo/155-mm-he-er-fb-bb-ofd-m3-dv/ |archive-date=15 July 2022 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220715081144/https://www.msm.sk/en/what-we-do/defence/ammunition/artillery-ammo/155-mm-he-er-fb-bb-ofd-m3-dv/ |url-status= dead}}</ref>{{irrelevant citation|date=July 2024|reason=Unrelated manufacturer's claim about specific shell; no mention of CAESAR}} or targets over {{cvt|55|km|mi}} away using rocket-assisted or smart ammunition.{{citation needed|date=July 2024}}

The CAESAR was developed by French defence contractor GIAT Industries (now [[KNDS France]]) and has been exported to various countries. Units manufactured for the [[French Army]] use a 6×6 [[Renault Sherpa 5]] chassis,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/294250179|title=Renault Sherpa chassis chosen for CAESAR|website=ResearchGate}}</ref><ref>{{cite interview |last=Izard |first=Laurent |subject-link= |interviewer=Ronan Planchon |title=Pulls militaires fabriqués au Maroc: «Le gouvernement a le devoir moral de choisir, à qualité d'offre équivalente, des producteurs français» |language=fr |trans-title=Military sweaters made in Morocco: 'Given products of equal quality, the government has the moral duty to choose French producers' |work=[[Le Figaro]] |date=5 November 2021 |publisher=[[Groupe Figaro]] |location=Paris |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/vox/economie/pulls-militaires-fabriques-au-maroc-le-gouvernement-a-le-devoir-moral-de-choisir-a-qualite-d-offre-equivalente-des-producteurs-francais-20211105 |access-date=21 June 2024 |quote=''Le canon automoteur Caesar (que nous venons de vendre à la Belgique) produit par Nexter, en constitue une parfaite illustration : son châssis, français, est un Renault Sherpa 5 d'Arquus (ex-Renault Trucks Defense)...En revanche, le châssis «export» est un Mercedes-Benz Unimog.'' |trans-quote=The Caesar self-propelled cannon (which we have just sold to Belgium), produced by Nexter, constitutes a perfect example: its French chassis is a Renault Sherpa 5 from Arquus (ex-Renault Trucks Defense)...On the other hand, its "export" chassis is a Mercedes-Benz Unimog.}}</ref> while some export customers have opted for systems integrated on a [[Unimog#1990s|6×6 Unimog U2450L]] or 8×8 [[Tatra 817]] chassis.<ref name="janes-foss">{{cite book
| last         = Foss
| first        = Christopher Frank
| author-link  = Christopher F Foss
| date         = 2011
